  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200\u00b0C (400\u00b0F).",
    "Toss dry chickpeas with 1 tbsp olive oil, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper. Spread on a baking sheet and roast for 25\u201130 minutes, stirring halfway, until golden and crispy.",
    "While chickpeas roast, combine tomatoes, cucumber, onion, olives, and grated pecorino in a large bowl.",
    "In a small bowl whisk together remaining 1 tbsp olive oil, lemon juice, oregano, a pinch of salt, and pepper to create the vinaigrette.",
    "Drizzle the vinaigrette over the salad, tossing gently to coat.",
    "Fold in roasted chickpeas and top with halved almonds for extra crunch.",
    "Serve immediately, optionally garnishing with fresh parsley or a drizzle of extra smoked olive oil.",
    "Enjoy the smoky, sour, and crispy flavors of this Greek pecorino salad."
